# pyenv
#   For a library or app, you might want to share your .python-version.
#   See https://github.com/pyenv/pyenv/issues/530
#.python-version

# pipenv
#   According to pypa/pipenv#598, it is recommended to include Pipfile.lock in version control.
#   However, in case of collaboration, if platform is not identical, the lock file will prevent install;
#   alternative is to use Bare Pipfile without lock.
#Pipfile.lock

# poetry
#   Similar to Pipenv, poetry.lock contains the resolved dependencies, which is recommended to commit.
#   https://python-poetry.org/docs/basic-usage/#commit-your-poetrylock-file-to-version-control
#poetry.lock

# pdm
#   Similar to Poetry and Pipenv, pdm.lock contains resolved dependencies for the project.
#   https://pdm-project.org/latest/usage/dependency/
#pdm.lock

# lsvirtualenv
#   Official virtualenvwrapper keys
#virtualenvwrapper

# PEP 582; used by e.g. github.com/pdm-project/pdm
__pypackages__/

